  "conditionals": 57,
  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "Outer membrane protein (OMP) assembly in E. coli requires the BAM (\u03b2-barrel assembly machinery) complex to insert \u03b2-barrel proteins into the outer membrane. OMPs are synthesized in cytoplasm, translocated through SecYEG to periplasm as unfolded polypeptides bound by chaperones (SurA, Skp, DegP), delivered to BAM complex (BamA + BamBCDE), and inserted into outer membrane. BamA is the central insertase, a \u03b2-barrel itself. The process requires precise recognition of \u03b2-barrel signature motifs.",
  "id": "ecoli_outer_membrane_assembly",
  "keywords": [
    "outer membrane",
    "BAM complex",
    "BamA",
    "\u03b2-barrel",
    "OMP",
    "SurA",
    "Skp"
  ],
